PURPOSE:-
--------
This scenario is to test a specific a case of LSA age reaches to maximum(3600 seconds).


SCENARIO:-
---------
Scenarios contains 6 nodes whose node ids are 42, 80, 302, 304, 404 and 1042.

Nodes-42 and 80 are in wireless subnet-1.
Nodes-302 and 304 are in wireless subnet-2.

CBR is used to send data segments from
Node-404 to Node-1042


Topology:-
---------

      (1042)-----(42).......(80)-----(302).....(304)-----(404)

<----> represents wired link.
<....> represents wireless link.


RUN:-
----
Run '<QUALNET_HOME>/bin/qualnet max-lsa-age-increment-interval-nssa-area.config'.


DESCRIPTION OF THE FILES:-
-------------------------
1. max-lsa-age-increment-interval-nssa-area.app -  QualNet configuration file for application input.
2. max-lsa-age-increment-interval-nssa-area.config - QualNet configuration input file.
3. max-lsa-age-increment-interval-nssa-area.nodes - QualNet node placement file for the simulation run.
4. max-lsa-age-increment-interval-nssa-area.expected.stat - QualNet statistics collection.
5. max-lsa-age-increment-interval-nssa-area.member - QualNet multicast group members file.
5. max-lsa-age-increment-interval-nssa-area.ospf - Ospf area configuration file
6. max-lsa-age-increment-interval-nssa-area.router-config - QualNet router configuration file.
6. max-lsa-age-increment-interval-nssa-area.routes-default - QualNet default routes file.
7. README - This file.
